President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Kansas and has ordered Federal assistance to supplement State and local recovery efforts. The assistance is for areas affected by severe storms, straight-line winds, tornadoes, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from April 28, 2019, onwards. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The funding will also be available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Jon K. Huss has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the State and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.